Uitenhage The Uitenhage Regional Court sentenced a 28-year-old man to 20 years imprisonment for raping a 10-year-old boy in Uitenhage, Eastern Cape police said on Wednesday. Spokesperson Captain Gerda Swart said said that Clinton Killian was sentenced on Tuesday. &quot;He was found guilty on a charge of rape on December 9, 2016 and sentenced on January 31. Members from the South African Police Service will remain committed and work tirelessly to ensure that perpetrators who commit crimes against women and children are brought to book,&quot; Swart said. Killian was accused of raping the boy on July 31, 2015, in an open field and was arrested by the Family Violence Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit in Uitenhage on the same day and he remained in custody for the duration of the trial. African News Agency